    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p><addressee>Revd. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Balto.</placeName>
                <date>Dec. 17/62</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have send you the<lb/>
                <date>13th</date> of last month the small amount which<lb/> I owed you for the
                Catechisms<lb/> &amp; requested you to send me<lb/> some other religious books.<lb/>
                Now I am very surprised that<lb/> you have since that time<lb/> neither received
                answer from<lb/> you, nor the books, of which I<lb/> could have already sold a
                good<lb/> part in my <sic>shool</sic>.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I request you therefore to let<lb/> me know whether you have<lb/> received my letter
                in which the<lb/> money was <sic>inclosed</sic> or not, &amp; in<lb/> case you have
                received it to<lb/> forward me the named books.</p>
            <p>Wishing that these lines may<lb/> meet you by best health, I<lb/> remain as ever</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Your faithful friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">A. Guinzburg</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P.S. You can give the books to be<lb/> sent for me to <persName>Mess E. H. Butler
                    &amp; Co.</persName> Booksellers in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>, to<lb/>
                send them to <persName>Messr T. W. Bard &amp; Co.</persName> here.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
